INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (85,477,4,'Great location walking distance to NRG Stadium. Next door to Pappa BBQ (warning- good, but very smoky flavor). Hotel was nicely decorated, gave a warm welcome. Front desk staff was friendly, though distracted. Our room, while quite large (we had an accessible room), had two ACs that did not de-humidify the room. It felt damp/humid the whole stay. Though... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (86,478,2,'The room was clean, the hotel workers were very good and the breakfast was also good. But the kennel with the dogs was awful. These dogs starting barking at six in the morning. The television in my room was a twenty inch LG. I will never go back there again.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (87,479,5,'Only .3 (three tenths!) of a mile away from the Kirby St. gate of NRG Stadium. It can even be considered walking distance, and you avoid the price of parking! How nice it is to be so nearby after attending an exciting event at NRG Stadium.....saving the possibly long drive home, or to the airport, for the next day.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (88,480,5,'On our two trips prior to this one both the breakfast and the internet were below par. I am glad to report that on our most recent trip the internet worked great and the breakfast was much improved. When you go to Texas for cancer treatment, the little things become big things. You can stay here with confidence.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (89,481,4,'Stayed here for two nights to visit MDA. The rooms are clean. The bed is comfortable. The internet worked great. The staff was nice. Close to many restaurants. I highly recommend. We stayed at Best Western the last visit and had a total different (bad) experience.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (90,482,4,'I was a bit concerned after checking the rating of this hotel, but was so pleasantly surprised when I got there. I was basically there for a medical visit and it seemed like so were a lot of other people, but we would totally stay there if we were just visiting Houston. My mom checked in for me since I... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (91,483,4,'We stay here each time my husband has a medical appt in Houston and they do offer medical rates if you ask. It is near medical center off of Main St. Very quiet and very clean large rooms. Several eating places within walking distance. Offers medical center shuttle also. The pool is very small, but we don''t use that anyways... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (92,484,1,'Visited the comfort suites in new iberia louisiana and my daughters head was almost decapitated in the elivator. When i talked to the front desk to make a complaint and get the front desk to give me the corporate information she gave me a cell phone number instead of the corporate office . We called numerous times before an answer... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (93,485,5,'I have been staying here, off and on, four about 7 years. The first time was when my father was going thru treatment at MD Anderson. The staff were great, made accommodations for him and also for his caregivers. They were also very understanding for those going thru treatments also local hospitals. I have also stayed there during my pre... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (94,486,4,'Very nice, like new lobby and rooms. Lobby and halls have tile floors that look great. Fancy, large chandelier in lobby. Hotel is 13 years old but looked like it was remodeled recently. Near Rice University. Had a security guard on duty. Fridge in our room was noisy. Dual phone charger ports by bed and on desk. Lots of digital... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (95,487,4,'The hotel was great, staff was great only bad thing was the breakfast as I am a choice hotel guy and most of the comfort suites have a great breakfast this one kinda lacked. But Staff and rest of the hotel was great');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (96,488,3,'We stayed here because of a family medical emergency.Did not have any options for a room. We had the SMALL queen room--think it may have been laundry area previously. Bed fair. Room quite. Was OK for one night. This hotel is near the stadium. Price was ok .99 plus tax.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (97,489,3,'This is the old address for Thunderbird. The new one is:Thunderbird School of Global Management1 Global PlaceGlendale, AZ 85306-6000 USASee their website:http://www.thunderbird.edu/about_thunderbird/contact_us.htm');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (100,492,3,'The room was fine and the mattress was very comfortable. Unfortunately, I arrived while the front entrance was under-construction. There was not sufficient signage to find out how to enter the building. I would have left, had I not already had a reservation through Hotels.com.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (101,493,2,'Reprehensible three days without maid service despite telling the management after it had happened the first time. I would not recommend this hotel for this reason.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (102,494,2,'The pictures on the web site were more expensive looking then the reality. We were told we had one of the best rooms, besides staring at cargo containers, the TV would not work so they changed our room. It was not well furnished and we could not regulate the air conditioner (way too warm for sleeping). The continental breakfast was good and the staff was very nice and helpful. The linens were harsh and uncomfortable. Sorry, but this was not at all what I expected and it was certainly unacceptable.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (103,495,4,'The didn''t tell me they were gonna run my credit card for accidental for a 100 charge. They just told me they had to double check my ID and the credit card that was used.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (104,496,4,'I stayed here with some girlfriends for a wine tasting getaway. The staff pointed out some great wineries and restaurants and were very friendly.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (105,560,5,'Beautiful hotel. Very clean and service was great. This is a must stay and if I''m in need of a hotel in the Livermore area, this is the place to stay.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (106,561,2,'The room was big and the hotel staff were nice, but I couldn''t get over the smelly linens. When I lay down on the bed, all I could smell was dirty old sweat socks! I don''t think they ever used detergent or fabric softener to wash the linens!They were that horrible! I had to spray the linens with perfume so I wouldn''t smell them ''au naturel'' while I''m sleeping! I''m never going to stay in this hotel ever again!');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (107,562,5,'Nice place no complaints, one thing they didn''t tell me,is they put a 100 hold on your card that stays for a couple days after you check out. I know this is not rare but any place that does has told me. I ended up calling trying to get it refunded. The breakfast in morning was pretty good, they had a full buffet not just some pakage pastries. Leave your swimsuit at home though the pool is small very small.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (108,563,5,'Great stay for our night downtown Livermore at Bankhead Theater concert. Birthday celebration for friend. The most comfortable bed ever! Nice patio where we spent our morning catching up. Hotel under construction did not bother us.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (109,564,5,'Perfect for my family to relax for the Easter weekend and for my girlfriend''s Livermore 1/2 marathon!');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (110,565,4,'The hotel was great. There was little construction going on which altered where they served breakfast, but it didn''t bother us any.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (111,566,3,'Having never been to Livermore, imagine my shock when the 2nd floor balcony room overlooked a parking lot and a gas station with a Jack in the Box thrown in for good measure. I thought I was staying in wine country. It would also have been nice to know that it is under construction. Granted I should have done more research but it was a last minute decision to go. The only good thing I could say is the bed was comfortable. If you are looking for a hotel right off of a freeway this one fits the bill, although way overpriced.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (112,567,3,'The bathroom sink splashes water, need to be fixed. The bathtub/shower make loud noises. Other than that, it was a good stay.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (113,568,5,'Great');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (114,569,3,'Nice in/out along the freeway. I thought it was a little high for what it was.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (115,570,3,'Beds and pillows were nice. And the television was good as well. The pool was closed.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (116,571,5,'My husband and I thoroughly enjoyed our stay here. The staff were friendly, helpful and efficient. The breakfast in the morning was delicious with a good selection of food and beverages. We will definitely stay here again and refer friends and family too.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (117,572,5,'Close to freeway on/off ramp. enjoyed the stay');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (118,573,2,'This hotel was promoted as being in the wine country. However, it was a block from the freeway. When we asked the desk clerk about this, she pointed her finger toward the door and said, It''s about 4 miles that way. We had a great view of Jack in the Box parking lot. When we first entered our room and kicked off our shoes, we found ourselves stepping on numerous sand burrs left on the carpet. After working out and returning to our room at 9am, there was no hot water for the shower. The breakfast was adequate and the housekeeping staff were friendly.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (119,574,5,'Came for concert at Wente. Last time I traveled to area the accomodations had a shuttle service. That would be a nice amenity if you could add it. Great clean place to stay.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (120,575,4,'Only problem we had was that we were not informed of the teen basketball tournament going on in the city. As a result, lots of kids, the room next to ours had the TV blaring until midnight and then on again a 5 am. We went to the lobby for our full breakfast at 10:15 and there was nothing left. We pickup a beagle and coffee and went to our room. They should have planned ahead for all the teens to eat all the food. There was 45 minutes left for breakfast time but nothing to eat. Outside of that, our stay was very nice. The gentleman at the front desk was especially cordial and accommodating.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (121,576,4,'It was cold in the room. We couldn''t get the heater on easily for some reason but then when the heat temperature finally came on we were sweating in the middle of the night. I would like a better thermostat or better direction. The hot breakfast was great!!!');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (122,577,3,'All the rooms have been recently renovated. They are in the process of renovating the lobby area. The room was new and clean. The beds were very comfortable. The bed linen looks new too. Its also nice to have electrical sockets at desk level and plenty of them. The breakfast was so so... eggs, sausages and hashbrown (no fruits) but barely edible.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (123,578,5,'Let''s face it, this is NOT in the Livermore ''wine country''....you can throw a rock from your room to busy InterState 580 and never come close to a vine or vineyard!');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (124,579,4,'It was OK . they paid for the ice I purached.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (125,580,5,'I must say the GM at this hotel Catherine is the bomb! She was very attentive and helpful. The hotel was very clean and the staff were all very nice to us from the moment we walked in the door. I would stay here every time I''m in California. Thanks again Cat!');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (126,581,4,'The hotel was great, but the Buffet Breakfast was the worst I have ever had! The bacon taste like cardboard, eggs and sausage were cold, Pastries were hard and very little fruit. The only thing hot and worth eating was fixing yourself a waffle at the waffle machine if you didn''t mind waiting in line for it.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (127,582,4,'The Hawthorne Suites offers an affordable, comfortable environment that is convenient to the 580 freeway (just south of it) and within a mile and a half of downtown Livermore. Room was incredibly clean and comfortable. While they are currently going through a renovation, which I think will be really nice once it is completed, we rarely had any indication of the ongoing construction activities. Staff was very friendly and accommodating.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (128,583,4,'My family stated the place was nice as they were here for my wedding. Location was great and only 10 minutes away from destinations.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (129,584,4,'Very comfortable rooms, will stay again when in the area.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (130,585,5,'Staff was great and rooms were clean and very comfortable.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (131,586,5,'Stayed at this hotel as part of a nearby wedding. I have to say I was impressed. Was greeted by Catherine at the front desk. I had spoke with her earlier before arriving and she was great on the phone and she was so sweet at check in. Very friendly, accommodating, and engaging. Really started the stay off right. The... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (132,587,5,'What a pleasant surprise! We are use to staying at expensive four star hotels but needed to complete a quick business trip and we were so delighted with this hotel. All newly remodeled, pleasant professional staff, and the hot breakfast was a perfect addition. Highly recommend and you will not be disappointed!');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (133,588,5,'The hotel is absolutely beautiful. We were very impressed by the dcor everything was clean and felt very upscale. The hotel is located near the freeway. There is a gas station, fast food, and shopping nearby. We were in town for a family event so we didn''t do much exploring, but there seemed to be many amenities right in the area. The best part was the proximity to downtown Livermore. Wonderful shopping and dining opportunities, and only 5 minutes away. Also, the wineries are within a 10 minute drive. All in all, a wonderful place to stay and lots to do in the area.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (134,589,3,'The most convenient place to stay in Livermor and where we will stay in the future.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (135,590,4,'Very nice for the price.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (136,591,4,'The room was clean, spacious, and the bed was extremely comfortable. We were in Livermore for a two-day stay, and it was a nice quiet retreat in the midst of family chaos.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (137,592,3,'All was great, until the heater/AC came on. It sounded like a vacuum cleaner every time it turned on. Waking me up over and over. The room would get to hot then to cold. Had a horrible night sleep. Vroom -- Vroom. Clean, friendly, comfy bed, all ruined by a Motel-6 quality wall unit.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (138,593,3,'There''s nothing wrong with the hotel except that there are flood lights shining in your window while you sleep and the curtains don''t close. I really like the furniture The bedding was clean the pillows are great. Next time I will ask for a room with windows on the other side.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (139,594,4,'The hotel itself was very nice. Staff was very helpful, especially with accommodating us when we asked to check in early. The problem was with cleanliness. Our room was not clean enough - I found a floss stick on the table in our room. What looked like a condom was found when we went to use the spa. And the pool was full of leaves and dirt on the bottom. Otherwise, our room would have been great. Very large with everything you need for a comfortable stay. Nice large screen tv as well - made my husband happy.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (140,595,2,'Mediocre. The carpets and elevator reek of sour wine. Evidently they have regular wine Thursdays here. Service was somewhat lacking. I requested a wakeup call, they didn''t do it. Finally, the free breakfast was on the poor side. Daddy, this bacon tastes like tuna.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (141,596,5,'Nice experience, despite the re-modeling construction. Friendly and courteous hotel staff. Beautiful new room decor and ambience.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (142,660,5,'One night only, but a nice one. New renno''s high quality throughout. Comfy, modern accomodation. Our room overlooked grazing cattle and the relentless I-580, so it was busy, but totally silent. We''ll be back.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (143,661,5,'Guy at front desk was a jerk, smart Alec');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (144,662,5,'When I made reservations at this hotel, I had average expectations at that that price rate for that area. However the newly renovated room, the professional staff and the cleanliness and the comfort of really surprised me and I will definitely go back.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (145,663,2,'We stayed for two nights. The lobby was nice and the breakfast was good. However, the room was not properly cleaned upon arrival and the same issues remained on the second day. Would have expected much better at this price.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (146,664,5,'I have stayed here twice now and loved it both times. Staff are very courteous and welcoming. The pool can use an upgrade but we still had a great time lounging next to the pool.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (147,665,5,'Clean, safe, friendly, brand new, hotel- :)');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (148,666,2,'The last time I stayed at this hotel, it was under remodeling and one of the rooms I was placed in had a heating unit that did not work. I moved to another room, which was okay, but not as nice a room. This time, my granddaughter and I checked in at about 4:30 p.m. and the room was extremely... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (149,667,5,'Visiting family');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (150,668,5,'Perfect, best hotel over others in the area');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (151,669,3,'The hotel is under renovation so lobby and other areas were blocked off. Room was very nice but breakfast were less than tasty.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (152,670,4,'Staff was very nice. Hotel is updating it''s lobby and reception area so there was a bit of construction. Did not hamper anything. Breakfast was fine, room was nice and quite spacious and again hotel employees were very nice.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (153,671,5,'Great hotel in a great neighborhood. Will definitely be staying here again. Room was very spacious. Free breakfast was great! It was raining so we didn''t get to use the pool but it seemed very nice. A little pricey but its a very nice hotel! Free wi-fi and free parking - additional pluses!');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (154,672,5,'Very comfortable and accommodating. From making our reservation to our time spent, the Hawthorn in Livermore was really nice. I did have to find the direct phone number to get assurance our needs would be met as the central hotel reservation system is simply not equipped to handle any details. Once accessed the staff was most gracious and reassuring and... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (155,673,4,'I work in Livermore and stayed the night to celebrate with friends. The location is close to downtown and the local wineries. My boyfriend and I were very pleased with the accommodations, the room was clean and large. The front desk was very friendly and helpful. I will stay here again.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (156,674,4,'A nice hotel, it was undergoing renovation when I stayed so shou be finished soon. Staff was helpful and friendly. Only complaint is the breakfast.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (157,675,5,'I live somewhat local in Redwood City, but it''s far enough away that after spending the evening with High School Friends, having a 30th gathering wasn''t an official reunion, at a local beer pub, we didn''t want to chance driving home after having a few beers. We made the reservation Friday night, and honestly, was apprehensive because of some of the reviews. Pleasantly surprised! The place was clean, it''s had a facelift and looks good. The bathroom tub could use an update...but I have stayed in the W in downtown Chicago and the tub was worse and room was horrible. I''d take this room over that one any day! The breakfast the next morning was good. Nothing to write home about, but it offers a great selection and the eggs weren''t watered down. Sausage was good...bacon...well, that looked and smelled like a dog treat. Passed on that one. But the coffee was decent and overall, was very pleased with our last minute choice to stay there...would do it again and would recommend others! It was 1/2 mile from the pub and right at the freeway, so leaving was easy, too.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (158,676,5,'Excellent Staff');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (159,677,5,'We booked this hotel because we had a wedding. It was impeccable, comfortable, and they had an excellent breakfast.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (160,678,5,'I was at the hotel for a wedding and all of the staff, Catherine in particular, were incredibly helpful and accommodating. I also loved that there were different types of pillows on the beds!');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (161,883,3,'Stayed here for a wedding weekend. Easily accessible from the freeway, 5min drive to downtown Livermore, good weekend stay for wine tasting or weddings, not much of a view in any direction. Rooms were clean with modern decor. Parking was free. Free continental breakfast. They were remodeling the dining area during our stay but it didn''t bother us too much.... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (162,884,5,'Very nice hotel and staff, the location was also perfect because it was easy to get to due being close freeway exit.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (163,885,2,'Our family reserved 6 rooms for 2-4 days for a family event. 3 of the 6 rooms had some significant disappointments, including blood and feces on the sheets, and roaches in the room. Our daughter turned her refrigerator on upon check in and then stocked it with food. Housekeeping turned it off and the food spoiled. Gentleman at the front... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (164,886,5,'Everything was good. The front desk staff was fine, but I thought they could''ve been a more friendly and welcoming.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (165,887,1,'Sheets were filthy, jacuzzi was freezing with bugs in it, the breakfast had options but the eggs and bacon tasted terrible!');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (166,888,4,'Wanted to check out their wine tasting, the wine trolly was fun and affordable, the wine was great, the food downtown was good, nice atmosphere. Our Hotel was conveniently located very close to everything we wanted to do. Got some great deals at the outlets, which were close by, as well. Great weekend stay.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (167,889,2,'The pillows were way too soft without pillowcases. The mattress was so soft my back was aching. When i awoke in the am since I arrived so late and did not notice I flipped the covers off and there was dried blood on the sheets. I could not leave fast enough. Sorry but never again. The next night I stayed... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (168,890,4,'Clean, comfortable room. Breakfast was good. Coffee not bad. The bacon was weird. Soy maybe Kinda gross. Many people threw it away. Everything else was fine. Not over the top amazing, but I think I got my money''s worth.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (169,891,3,'Super solid, well-maintained but nothing to write home about. Breakfast buffet, while complimentary was pretty lackluster, but a nice feature nonetheless.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (170,892,5,'I frequently go to Livermore for business travel and always stay at this hotel. The hotel is always clean, beds are super comfy, staff is friendly, free breakfast in the morning and wine in the evening. What else could you ask for when you are traveling');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (171,893,5,'Stayed for a week - from early check-in assistance to excellent accommodations, it was all I could hope for in a multi-day business stay.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (172,894,4,'one night stay to attend concert/dinner at winery');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (173,895,4,'This hotel has a great, friendly staff, clean rooms, comfy beds and pillows and the price is right. Would stay there again when I am in town.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (174,896,3,'I expected more from a Wyndham hotel......bathroom was very small, not enough counter space for makeup bag and shaving kit. Amenities were not replenished. Had to ask for coffee replacements, then were given single serve bags for a 4 cup coffee maker! Coffee maker eventually replaced, but I had to ask... twice! And the word suite. Is not too accurate.... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (175,960,5,'My husband and I came out here from Tennessee for a business conference / couples getaway. It''s our first full day here and I''m already so impressed with this hotel! The hotel and the room are both clean and pretty . The staff is super friendly and the front desk girl even printed out a map of things I might... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (176,961,5,'We have always chosen this hotel for location and comfort, as well as value. Now with updated decor we love it even more. There was even a chaise lounge with a computer table, as well as lots of outlets for our electronics. Front staff is always helpful and polite.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (177,962,4,'excellent service and location for wedding party. staff worked hard at accommodating numerous guests.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (178,963,3,'The hotel was fine, I with the shower (specifically the shower head) was cleaner, it could you a thorough scrubbing and white vinegar cleaning.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (179,964,5,'We found this hotel because of its connection to the Livermore Shakespeare Festival. They offered a dinner-theater-hotel package that was perfect for our first time at this venue. The hotel is conveniently located close enough to the freeway to be easily accessible but far enough away to be out of the traffic noise. The Hawthorn staff were very pleasant and... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (180,965,4,'Fun overnight stay');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (181,966,1,'My boyfriend and I stayed here for two nights for a wedding in Livermore in July. I wouldn''t recommend this hotel to my worst enemy. There is absolutely no excuse for stealing my friend''s personal belongings whom were also staying at this hotel the same nights. I left my cell phone charger in room 305 and came back a few... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (182,967,5,'My husband and I stayed at the Hawthorne Suites by Wyndham Livermore,CA. for my daughter''s wedding, as did many of their guests. It was wonderful! We got the room with 2 queen beds and they were so comfortable! I have a very bad back and they had such comfort and support. The pillows were the best pillows I had ever... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (183,968,1,'I have never in my life been treated so terribly . I was kicked out Of the hotel due to stained sheets and a carpet stain, was charged for every accusation and still asked to leave . I was even escorted by the police out of the hotel. This was about money. I was charged for something I didn''t receive.... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (184,969,3,'Our room was on the ground floor, facing the parking lot. This meant that any time our curtains were open, we were on display for whoever was walking/driving by. It also meant we couldn''t safely leave our window(s) open at night and had to rely on the very, very loud air conditioner. Although outdated, our room was very reasonable. There... More');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (185,970,4,'Came to Binghamton to visit with a relative. Fairfield Inn is a convenient location. Nearby is Ostinango Park which is great for walking or running.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (186,971,5,'Great Experience. Nice Staff clean rooms good free breakfast');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (187,972,4,'Not a lot of options where I needed to stay for work, but this hotel was nice. Fairly updated and the staff was friendly. Walking distance to Cracker Barrel and Applebee''s, which was nice. Other restaurants within driving distance. Easy to get to, right off interstate. If I was back in town for work, I''d stay here again for sure.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (188,973,1,'This hotel is undergoing construction. Banging and other loud noises begin early in the morning. Forget about enjoying a peaceful morning.Was very disappointed by the reaction of the hotel staff when I brought it to their attention. A free night''s stay or at least a discount on my next stay may have helped the situation. Dont book this hotel until the construction is complete');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (189,974,5,'Good Location, right off highway. Applebees next door...you can walk there! Hallway was dirty but the roomwas very clean and comfortable.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (190,975,5,'The hotel was fairly new and slightly out of town. The pool was refreshing. Breakfast was adequate but as usual in hotels like this, when crowded jockeying for a spot to sit can be a challenge.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (191,976,3,'Rooms are very small, especially for a family of 4. Beds were not very comfortable and the bathroom was also small (straddle the toilet to close the door small). The pool area was not so great. Hot tub was cloudy and the whole area had a septic smell.');
INSERT INTO review(id,bookingId,Rating,comment) VALUES (192,977,5,'Needs more ice machines.');
